iplinary field of design research and proposes a new ethical agenda for designers and researchers that encompasses the responsibility to users, the problems of sustainability, and the complicated questions of how to set boundaries for applying advanced technology to solve the problems of human life. Opinionated and erudite, Victor Margolin's The Politics of the Artificial breaks fresh ground in its call for a new approach to design research and practice. Designers, engineers, architects, anthropologists, sociologists, and historians will all benefit from its insights.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aDesignxHistoryy20th century. 7aDESIGN / General.2bisacsh  aessay collection, political, academic, scholarly, research, designer, fake, art, artistic, commercial, product, styling, daily, life, turn of the century, time period, era, matrix, ken isaacs, reflection, ethical, ethics, sustainability, interdisciplinary, international, user, problems, engineer, architect, career, anthropologist, sociologist.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022650503940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226518374423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226518374/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles